TOTAL_PAGES: 1: You Should Own J&J, Zimmer Biomet Ahead Of Earnings: RBC
column7: With earnings season about to kick off in earnest tomorrow, RBC Capital Markets’Glenn Novarro takes a look at the medical device companies he covers, suggesting that investors own Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) and Zimmer Biomet Holdings (ZBH) going into the reports.  Novarro writes that these two stocks have the best risk-reward ahead of earnings, Johnson & Johnson has lagged its group for some time, and while sentiment has improved lately, he expects more multiple expansion for the stock, helped by a strong first quarter (along with its pending acquisition of Actelion, closing in June).  Zimmer Biomet is the cheapest of his large-cap tech stocks, and while he doesn’t expect the company’s first quarter to beat expectations, he writes that its valuation is so low that all it has to do is meet consensus to see gains.
